    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "A 3d tiled map sounds like a bit too much. Multiple layers are a good idea though. For the map format, we could simply add a new section to the `map.yaml`.\r\n```\r\nLayers:\r\n    Layer@hill:\r\n        Offset: 10\r\n    Layer@clouds:\r\n        Offset: 236\r\n```\r\nThe main layer has to be completely filled, always has the offset 0 and is saved in the file `map.bin`. The first additional layer is drawn 10 units above the ground layer and saved in the file `map_hill.bin` while the second one is drawn 236 units above the main layer and saved in the file `map_clouds.bin`. The information for the vertical collision should in the tileset like we currently do it for the horizontal \"collision\" information.\r\n\r\nThis would allow multiple layers without breaking the compatibility with older maps."
  },
